step_data.thought:
I've been zooming in on the map to reduce the area size for export, as the initial area was too large. Looking at the current page, I can see that the URL now shows 'map=10/42.8926/-74.1467', indicating we're at zoom level 10 (increased from level 9 in my previous action).

I can also see the current coordinates in the textboxes:
- North: 43.5854
- West: -74.7853
- East: -73.5081
- South: 42.1919

Looking at the page content, I can see there's still a message stating: 'This area is too large to be exported as OpenStreetMap XML Data. Please zoom in or select a smaller area...'

So I need to continue zooming in until the area becomes small enough for download. Let me click the 'Zoom In' button again to further increase the scale (zoom level).
